The paper proposes a new method for binary embedding that improves the time and space complexity of existing methods. This is a problem that is relevant to several areas of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), information theory (cs.IT), data structures (cs.DS), and multimedia (cs.MM). The paper includes experiments on image datasets, which further supports the relevance to computer vision. Therefore, cs.LG and cs.CV are the most likely categories, followed by cs.IT, cs.DS, and cs.MM.
